## âš™ï¸ Working Principle
1. A **propeller (fan)** draws polluted air into the system.
2. Air passes through the **main activated carbon filter**, removing pollutants.
3. An **air quality sensor** continuously monitors the quality of the filtered air.
4. When the air quality drops below a predefined threshold, the system detects **filter saturation**.
5. A **motor-driven mechanical mechanism** lowers the saturated main filter and lifts the **sub filter** into operation.
6. Air purification continues seamlessly using the sub filter until maintenance is performed.

